  2. Data Processing in the App
  
  The app only processes personal data as necessary and in accordance with the following legal bases under Art. 6 GDPR:
  
  Firebase Authentication: User ID (UID) for login. On Android, Google Sign-In is used; on iOS, Apple Sign-In is used.
  Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR
  
  Cloud Firestore: Stores bingo cards, draw data, event data, and UID for managing entries. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b)
  GDPR
  
  Local storage (Room on Android / SwiftData on iOS): Cards, draws, and settings are stored locally on the device. Legal
  basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR
  
  Text Recognition (OCR):
  
  - Android: ML Kit (on-device text recognition, no data sent to Google servers)
  - iOS: Apple Vision Framework (on-device text recognition)
  
  Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR
  
  Tesseract OCR (Android only): Local text recognition using open-source software. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR
  
  OpenCV (Android only): Image processing performed locally on the device to improve OCR accuracy. Legal basis: Art.
  6(1)(f) GDPR
  
  Object Detection (YOLO):
  
  - Android: TensorFlow Lite YOLO model (on-device)
  - iOS: CoreML YOLO model (on-device)
  
  No image data leaves the device for this processing. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR
  
  Gemini Cloud Scan (Ultra Scan): Used only after explicit user action and token consumption. Images are transmitted in
  encrypted form to Google servers for AI-based text extraction. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR
  
  Google AdMob: Ads are provided via the AdMob SDK. Personalized ads require explicit consent. If declined,
  non-personalized ads are shown. On iOS, App Tracking Transparency (ATT) permission is requested before personalized
  tracking. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (personalized), Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (non-personalized)
  
  Rewarded Ads: Optional video ads may be watched to unlock one-time benefits (e.g., additional card saves or scan
  tokens). Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR
  
  Firebase Analytics & Crashlytics: Used to improve app stability and understand usage patterns. Only pseudonymized data
  is processed. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR
  
  Firebase Remote Config: Used to control feature availability. Only anonymized device metadata is processed. Legal
  basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR
  
  Email support: If you contact us by email, your email address and message will be processed. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(a)
  GDPR
  
  In-App Purchases:
  
  - Android: Google Play Billing
  - iOS: Apple StoreKit / App Store
  
  Purchases (subscriptions, token packs, card packs) are processed via the respective platform. No payment data is
  stored in the app. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR
  
  Referral System: A unique, non-personal referral ID (MyID) can be shared. No personal data beyond the ID is exchanged
  between users. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR
  
  3. Hosting & Data Processing
  
  Data is processed through:
  
  - Google LLC, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA (Firebase services, Gemini API). Google is
  certified under the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework.
  - Apple Inc., One Apple Park Way, Cupertino, CA 95014, USA (Sign-In, StoreKit, on-device processing only – no user
  data transferred for local processing).
  
  Data is only transferred outside the EU when an adequate level of data protection is ensured under Art. 45 GDPR or
  appropriate safeguards exist under Art. 46 GDPR.
  
  4. Data Retention
  
  User data (e.g., UID and saved cards) is retained until manually deleted by the user. Ad consent can be changed at any
  time within the app. Support emails are deleted 90 days after resolution. Server logs are anonymized and stored for a
  maximum of 90 days for technical purposes. Analytics data is retained for up to 14 months by Firebase.
  
  5. Your Rights Under the GDPR
  
  You have the right to access, correct, delete or restrict the processing of your data, to object to processing, and to
  data portability. You can delete your data directly in the app under Settings → Account → "Delete Account & Data". You
  also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.
  
  6. App Tracking Transparency (iOS only)
  
  On iOS, the app requests your permission via Apple's App Tracking Transparency framework before any cross-app tracking
  occurs. You can change this permission at any time in your device settings under Settings → Privacy → Tracking.
  
  7. Consent Management
  
  The app uses Google's User Messaging Platform (UMP) to manage consent for personalized advertising in accordance with
  GDPR and the ePrivacy Directive. You can change your consent choices at any time in the app under Settings → Privacy
  Choices.
  
  8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
  
  This privacy policy may be updated due to legal, technical, or functional changes. The current version is always
